<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Tough" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Tough,</orth> 1) not soft and flexible, but stiff and un-impressible: <cit><quote>my t. senior,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 2, 10</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 2, 10</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 2, 10</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 2, 10</bibl><lb />2) not easily worn or broken: <cit><quote>we are --er than you can put us to't,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 15</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thy t. commixture melts,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.6.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 6, 6</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>O sides, you are too t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.200" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 200</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>upon the rack of this t. world,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.314" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 314</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>